==English==

===Adjective===
'''hurtful'''

# Tending to [[impair]] or [[damage]]; injurious; mischievous; [[occasion]]ing [[loss]] or [[injury]]; causing [[pain]] or [[suffering]].

====Quotations====
*'''1649''': [[w:John Milton|John Milton]], ''Eikonoklastes''
*: A good principle not rightly understood may prove as '''hurtful''' as a bad.
*'''1890''': George Henry Rohé, ''Text-book of hygiene''
*: Well-cultivated soils are often healthy; nor at present has it been proved that the use of manure is '''hurtful'''.

